---
import { brandSettings } from '../../scripts/brandSettings.js';
---
<section id="typography">
                <h2>Typography</h2>
                
                <!-- <div class="instruction-note">
                    <strong>Student Instructions</strong>
                    Update the CSS of this page to reflect your chosen fonts. Define your accessibility rules for sizing, line height, text alignment, and capitalization based on WCAG readability guidelines.
                </div>-->

                <h3>Typeface Selection</h3>
                <p><strong>Primary Typeface:</strong> {brandSettings.typography.primaryFont}</p>
                <p><strong>Secondary Typeface:</strong> {brandSettings.typography.secondaryFont}</p>
                
                <h3>Readability Standards</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Line Height:</strong> Body text must have a line height of at least {brandSettings.typography.lineHeight} to ensure readability.</li>
                    <li><strong>Paragraph Spacing:</strong> Spacing between paragraphs must be at least {brandSettings.typography.paragraphSpacing} times the font size.</li>
                    <li><strong>Alignment:</strong> </li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Body text and long passages should be left-aligned (ragged right).</li>
                            <li>Fully justified text should not be used for paragraphs.</li>
                            <li>Center-aligned text may be used sparingly for short elements, such as headlines, short hero statements, event titles, and short call to action lines.</li>
                        </ul>
                    <li><strong>Capitalization:</strong> </li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Most content should use sentence case, where only the first word and proper nouns are capitalized.</li>
                            <li>Headlines and section titles may use title case when appropriate.</li>
                            <li>All caps text should be used sparingly.</li>
                        </ul>
                </ul>

                <h3>Hierarchy Preview</h3>
                <div class="type-preview">
                    <h1>Red Bull (H1) - [40 px/Bold]</h1>
                    <h2>Branding (H2) - [32 px/Semibold]</h2>
                    <h3>Stylesheet (H3) - [24 px/Medium]</h3>
                    <p>Body Paragraph - [16 px/Regular]. Red Bull fuels moments of energy and adventure. From high-performance sports to creative culture, the brand supports individuals who push limits and redefine what is possible. Every initiative reflects the spirit of innovation, excitement, and the drive to keep moving forward.</p>
                </div>
            </section>